<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/781977-did-anyone-else-think-the-major-theme-or">Did anyone else think the major theme or &quot;horror&quot; of the book is repressed female (lesbian) sexuality?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_781977'><a id="like_count_community_question_781977" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/781977?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">141 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F89717.The_Haunting_of_Hill_House">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/781977-did-anyone-else-think-the-major-theme-or">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/781977-did-anyone-else-think-the-major-theme-or">See all 29 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/2634685-shira"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1454341049i/2634685._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/2634685-shira">Shira</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I don't know that anyone else mentioned that the elder Crain sister, a spinster, has a young woman from the village come and live with her. The compan<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I don't know that anyone else mentioned that the elder Crain sister, a spinster, has a young woman from the village come and live with her. The companion inherits the house when the elder sister dies. But the younger sister doesn't see her as worthy of owning the house and harasses her until she ends up killing herself. To me, the companion was the elder sister's lover and the younger sister didn't want to acknowledge that they had a familial relationship. The house is then imbued with resentful repressed same-sex sexual interest, which inflicts itself on Eleanor -- she picks up on the (not-so) subtle hints that Theodora has a lesbian partner (her "roommate") that she's fighting with, and thinks that her future will be following Theodora to her home and becoming her new lover. When that doesn't work for her, what choice does she have but to give herself the same ending the companion had?<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
